1. Environment Setup

First, we load the necessary packages for spatial dependence, data manipulation, and simulation.

# Install packages if not already installed
if (!require(spdep)) install.packages("spdep")
if (!require(MASS)) install.packages("MASS")
if (!require(dplyr)) install.packages("dplyr")
if (!require(tidyr)) install.packages("tidyr")

library(spdep)
library(MASS)
library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)

2. Spatial Grid Configuration

We set up a 10x10 grid representing 100 distinct clusters. We also define the spatial weights matrix using Queen contiguity (where neighbors share an edge or a vertex).

# Define 10x10 grid
grid_dim <- 10
N_clusters <- grid_dim^2
coords <- expand.grid(x = 1:grid_dim, y = 1:grid_dim)

# Create Queen contiguity weights matrix (W)
nb <- cell2nb(grid_dim, grid_dim, type = "queen")
W <- nb2mat(nb, style = "B", zero.policy = TRUE) # Binary adjacency matrix

3. Helper Functions

Here we define the functions to generate the 7 treatment assignment designs and the baseline incidence values (incorporating spatial dependence using a Uniform(0,1) noise distribution).

# Function to generate treatment assignment designs
get_designs <- function(design_id, n_resamples, N) {
  mat <- matrix(0, nrow = N, ncol = n_resamples)
  
  if (design_id == 1) {
    # Design 1: Checkerboard (Fixed at 2 possibilities)
    cb1 <- (coords$x + coords$y) %% 2
    cb2 <- 1 - cb1
    mat <- matrix(rep(c(cb1, cb2), length.out = N * n_resamples), ncol = n_resamples)
    
  } else if (design_id == 2) {
    # Design 2: Complete Randomization (CRD)
    for (i in 1:n_resamples) mat[, i] <- sample(c(rep(1, N/2), rep(0, N/2)))
    
  } else if (design_id == 3) {
    # Design 3: Block Randomization (2x2 spatial blocks)
    block_id <- paste((coords$x-1) %/% 2, (coords$y-1) %/% 2)
    unique_blocks <- unique(block_id)
    for (i in 1:n_resamples) {
      z <- numeric(N)
      for (b in unique_blocks) {
        idx <- which(block_id == b)
        z[idx] <- sample(c(1, 1, 0, 0)) # 2 treated, 2 control
      }
      mat[, i] <- z
    }
    
  } else if (design_id == 4) {
    # Design 4: Split-half (Fixed)
    split_z <- ifelse(coords$x <= grid_dim/2, 1, 0)
    mat <- matrix(rep(split_z, n_resamples), ncol = n_resamples)
    
  } else if (design_id == 5) {
    # Design 5: Row Randomization
    for (i in 1:n_resamples) {
      row_assignment <- sample(c(rep(1, grid_dim/2), rep(0, grid_dim/2)))
      mat[, i] <- row_assignment[coords$y]
    }
    
  } else if (design_id == 6) {
    # Design 6: Column Randomization
    for (i in 1:n_resamples) {
      col_assignment <- sample(c(rep(1, grid_dim/2), rep(0, grid_dim/2)))
      mat[, i] <- col_assignment[coords$x]
    }
    
  } else if (design_id == 7) {
    # Design 7: Random Alternating Diagonals
    diags <- coords$x + coords$y
    unique_diags <- unique(diags)
    for (i in 1:n_resamples) {
      diag_assign <- sample(c(1, 0), length(unique_diags), replace = TRUE)
      mat[, i] <- diag_assign[match(diags, unique_diags)]
    }
  }
  return(mat)
}

# Function to generate spatially correlated baseline using Uniform(0,1) noise
generate_baseline <- function(N, nb, rho) {
  I <- diag(N)
  inv_matrix <- solve(I - rho * nb2mat(nb, style="W", zero.policy=TRUE)) 
  epsilon <- runif(N, 0, 1) 
  Y0 <- as.vector(inv_matrix %*% epsilon)
  return(Y0)
}

4. Simulation Execution

This is the core execution block. We loop through all combinations of spatial dependence (\(\rho\)), spillover effect (\(\gamma\)), spillover type, and design type. Note: Depending on your hardware, this chunk may take several minutes to run.

# Simulation Parameters
n_designs_resamples <- 100
n_outcome_resamples <- 1000
rho_vals <- c(0.00, 0.01, 0.20, 0.50) 
gamma_vals <- c(0.5, 0.6, 0.7, 0.8)
spill_types <- c("control_only", "both")
design_ids <- 1:7
true_tau <- 1.0 # True intervention effect

results_list <- list()
list_index <- 1

# Calculate total scenarios for the progress tracker
total_scenarios <- length(rho_vals) * length(gamma_vals) * length(spill_types) * length(design_ids)

set.seed(2026)
start_time <- Sys.time()

cat("Starting simulation. Total scenarios to process:", total_scenarios, "\n")
## Starting simulation. Total scenarios to process: 224
cat("--------------------------------------------------------------\n")
## --------------------------------------------------------------
for (rho in rho_vals) {
  # Pre-generate baseline incidence samples
  Y0_matrix <- replicate(n_outcome_resamples, generate_baseline(N_clusters, nb, rho))
  
  for (gamma in gamma_vals) {
    for (spill_type in spill_types) {
      for (d_id in design_ids) {
        
        # --- PROGRESS TRACKER ---
        cat(sprintf("Processing %3d / %d | Design: %d | Rho: %.2f | Gamma: %.2f | Spill: %-12s\n", 
                    list_index, total_scenarios, d_id, rho, gamma, spill_type))
        flush.console() # Ensures the output prints immediately in some R IDEs
        
        Z_matrix <- get_designs(d_id, n_designs_resamples, N_clusters)
        scenario_estimates <- numeric(n_designs_resamples * n_outcome_resamples)
        counter <- 1
        
        for (d_resample in 1:n_designs_resamples) {
          Z <- Z_matrix[, d_resample]
          
          # Compute spillover indicator (Queen neighbors)
          has_treated_neighbor <- as.numeric((W %*% Z) > 0)
          
          if (spill_type == "control_only") {
            spill_effect <- gamma * has_treated_neighbor * (1 - Z)
          } else {
            spill_effect <- gamma * has_treated_neighbor
          }
          
          # Simulated outcomes vectorized across 1000 baseline samples
          Y_sim <- Y0_matrix + (true_tau * Z) + spill_effect
          
          # Edge cases (all treated or all control)
          if (sum(Z) == 0 || sum(Z) == N_clusters) {
            ate_est <- rep(NA, n_outcome_resamples) 
          } else {
            # Difference in Means Estimator
            mean_Y_trt <- colMeans(Y_sim[Z == 1, , drop = FALSE])
            mean_Y_ctrl <- colMeans(Y_sim[Z == 0, , drop = FALSE])
            ate_est <- mean_Y_trt - mean_Y_ctrl
          }
          
          # Store estimates
          idx_start <- counter
          idx_end <- counter + n_outcome_resamples - 1
          scenario_estimates[idx_start:idx_end] <- ate_est
          counter <- idx_end + 1
        }
        
        valid_estimates <- na.omit(scenario_estimates)
        
        # Calculate Metrics
        results_list[[list_index]] <- data.frame(
          Design = paste("Design", d_id),
          Rho = rho,
          Gamma = gamma,
          Spillover_Type = spill_type,
          Mean_Estimate = mean(valid_estimates),
          Bias = mean(valid_estimates) - true_tau,
          SD = sd(valid_estimates),
          MSE = mean((valid_estimates - true_tau)^2)
        )
        list_index <- list_index + 1
      }
    }
  }
}

5. Results Aggregation

Finally, we aggregate the granular dataset to evaluate overall efficacy (sorted by minimizing Mean Squared Error) and efficacy stratified by how spillover is applied.

# Overall Efficacy by Design
high_level_results <- granular_results %>%
  group_by(Design) %>%
  summarise(
    Avg_Bias = mean(Bias),
    Avg_SD = mean(SD),
    Avg_MSE = mean(MSE),
    Min_MSE = min(MSE),
    Max_MSE = max(MSE)
  ) %>%
  arrange(Avg_MSE) 

print("HIGH-LEVEL SUMMARY: OVERALL EFFICACY BY DESIGN")
## [1] "HIGH-LEVEL SUMMARY: OVERALL EFFICACY BY DESIGN"
print(high_level_results, width = Inf)

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# PLOT 1: Overall Design Robustness (Distribution of MSE)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
plot_mse_overall <- ggplot(granular_results, aes(x = reorder(Design, MSE, FUN = median), y = MSE, fill = Design)) +
  geom_boxplot(alpha = 0.8, outlier.alpha = 0.5) +
  scale_fill_viridis_d(option = "turbo") +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 14) +
  labs(
    title = "Overall Distribution of Estimation Error (MSE)",
    subtitle = "Aggregated across all spatial dependence and spillover scenarios",
    x = "Sampling Design",
    y = "Mean Squared Error (Lower is Better)"
  ) +
  theme(
    legend.position = "none",
    axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1),
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank()
  )

print(plot_mse_overall)

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# PLOT 2: MSE Breakdown by Spillover Magnitude and Target (Line Trend)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Reverted to the line chart showing average MSE trends as spillover intensifies.
mse_gamma_summary <- granular_results %>%
  group_by(Design, Gamma, Spillover_Type) %>%
  summarise(Avg_MSE = mean(MSE), .groups = "drop")

plot_mse_spillover <- ggplot(mse_gamma_summary, aes(x = Gamma, y = Avg_MSE, color = Design, group = Design)) +
  geom_line(linewidth = 1.2) +
  geom_point(size = 3) +
  facet_wrap(~ Spillover_Type, labeller = as_labeller(c(
    "both" = "Spillover to Both Treated & Control", 
    "control_only" = "Spillover to Control Only"
  ))) +
  scale_color_viridis_d(option = "turbo") +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 14) +
  labs(
    title = "Estimation Error vs. Spillover Magnitude",
    subtitle = "How designs degrade as spillover becomes more severe",
    x = "Spillover Magnitude (\u03b3)",
    y = "Average Mean Squared Error (MSE)",
    color = "Design"
  ) +
  theme(
    legend.position = "bottom",
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank()
  )

print(plot_mse_spillover)

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# PLOT 3: Heatmap of MSE by Spatial Dependence (rho) with Raw Values
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# We summarize the data and add a text_color column so the numbers remain 
# readable against the varying background colors of the heatmap.
mse_rho_summary <- granular_results %>%
  group_by(Design, Rho, Spillover_Type) %>%
  summarise(Avg_MSE = mean(MSE), .groups = "drop") %>%
  # Dynamically assign text color: black for high MSE (bright tiles), white for low (dark tiles)
  mutate(text_color = ifelse(Avg_MSE > quantile(Avg_MSE, 0.75), "black", "white"))

plot_mse_heatmap <- ggplot(mse_rho_summary, aes(x = as.factor(Rho), y = Design, fill = Avg_MSE)) +
  geom_tile(color = "white", linewidth = 0.5) +
  # Add the raw MSE values on top of the tiles
  geom_text(aes(label = sprintf("%.3f", Avg_MSE), color = text_color), size = 3.5, fontface = "bold", show.legend = FALSE) +
  facet_wrap(~ Spillover_Type, labeller = as_labeller(c(
    "both" = "Spillover to Both", 
    "control_only" = "Spillover to Control Only"
  ))) +
  scale_fill_viridis_c(option = "magma") + 
  scale_color_identity() + # Tells ggplot to use the literal colors from the text_color column
  theme_minimal(base_size = 14) +
  labs(
    title = "Heatmap of Error by Spatial Dependence",
    subtitle = "Interaction between Design and background spatial clustering (\u03c1)",
    x = "Spatial Dependence (\u03c1)",
    y = "Sampling Design",
    fill = "Avg MSE"
  ) +
  theme(
    panel.grid = element_blank(),
    axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 0, hjust = 0.5)
  )

print(plot_mse_heatmap)
